Abstract: No matter what strategy managers choose, cross-national differences in states&apos; strategic capabilities and objectives affect multinational corporations&apos; capabilities to manage interdependent operations. In this paper, we develop four attribute dimensions along which states&apos; strategic economic capabilities vary. We then apply these dimensions to show how they contribute to familiar international business models of managerial process, MNC strategy and organizational structure, and country competitiveness.&copy; 1994 JIBS. Journal of International Business Studies (1994) 25, 513&ndash;535
